    list UlDataSplitUeCfg {
      description "Additional definitions from MOM:min/max-elements:0/8; Uplink PDCP data split UE configuration group. Instance UlDataSplitUeCfg=Base is created automatically when parent MO instance is created, unless created manually in same transaction. Each UE configuration group identifier can only be defined in one ueConfGroupList among UlDataSplitUeCfg instances contained under parent UlDataSplit instance. Any combination of one UE group identifier in ueGroupList and one preference UE group identifier in prefUeGroupList must be unique among UlDataSplitUeCfg instances contained under parent UlDataSplit instance. Attributes prefUeGroupList, ueGroupList and ueConfGroupList must be empty in instance UlDataSplitUeCfg=Base but cannot all be empty in any other instance of UlDataSplitUeCfg under same parent UlDataSplit instance. Precondition: Instance UlDataSplitUeCfg=Base can only be created in same transaction as parent MO instance and cannot be deleted unless parent MO instance is deleted. Other instances can be created and deleted at any time. Maximum 7 UlDataSplitUeCfg instances, with RDN different from Base, can be created under parent MO instance.";
      key "ulDataSplitUeCfgId";
