  grouping UeMobilityGroupDefinition-attributes {
    leaf chipsetRef {
      description "Reference to an instance of Chipsets MO. Special <Value> \"ref\" for <Variable> chipset in selectionCriteria represents chipset <ValueList> defined via this reference. If empty, represented chipset <ValueList> is empty..";
      type string;
    }
    leaf imeiSvRef {
      description "Reference to an instance of ImeiSvs MO. Special <Value> \"ref\" for <Variable> imeisv in selectionCriteria represents imeisv <ValueList> defined via this reference. If empty, represented imeisv <ValueList> is empty..";
      type string;
    }
    leaf selectionCriteria {
      description "UE mobility group selection criteria. Defines selection criteria that UE needs to fulfill to belong to UE mobility group instance. If selection criteria evaluates to True, UE fulfills UE mobility group instance. If selection criteria evaluates to False or Unknown, UE does not fulfill UE mobility group instance. If selection criteria evaluates to True for more than one UE mobility group instance, UE belongs to UE mobility group instance with highest setting of ueMobilityGroupPriority. Syntax: ====== The syntax of selection criteria is defined using Backus-Naur form. <SelectionCriteria> ::= <ParentExpressionList> | \"\" <ParentExpressionList> ::= <ParentExpressionList> <AndOr> < ParentExpressionList> | <Not>? \"(\" <ParentExpressionList> \")\" | <ExpressionList> | <FlowExpressionList> <FlowExpressionList> ::= <FlowExpressionList> <AndOr> <FlowExpressionList> | <Not>? <FlowExpression> <FlowExpression> ::= \"[\"<ExpressionList>\"]\" <ExpressionList> ::= <ExpressionList> <AndOr> <ExpressionList> | <Not>? \"(\" <ExpressionList> \")\" | <Not>? <VariableExpression> <VariableExpression> ::= <Variable> <RelationalOperator> <Value> | <Variable> \"==\" \"{\" <ValueList> \"}\" <ValueList> ::= <Value> \",\" <ValueList> | <Value> <Variable> ::= \"5qi\" | \"arp\" | \"cgrole\" | \"chipset\" | \"imeisv\" | \"imeisvn\" | \"imeitac\" | \"pagingPrio\" | \"pCellOnlyUe\" | \" \"plmn\" | \"qci\" | \"redCapUe\" | \"rfsp\" | \"rrcEstResCause\" | \"snssai\" | \"spid\" | \"voNrUe\" <AndOr> ::= \"&&\" | \"||\" <Not> ::= \"!\" <RelationalOperator> ::= \"==\" | \"!=\" | \"<\" | \"<=\" | \">=\" | \">\" A list of possible values can be specified in the form <Variable> == {<value1>, <value2>, ... , <valueN>}. This statement is equivalent to writing (<Variable> == <value1> || <Variable> == <value2> || ... || <Variable> == <valueN>). Up to 4 <FlowExpression> can be defined in <SelectionCriteria>. Whitespaces are allowed in the string for improved readability and are removed prior to evaluation. Question mark (?) means zero or one occurrence. For example, <Not>? makes <Not> optional. Syntax is case sensitive. Semantic: ======== Selection criteria evaluation is defined by the following semantic rules. If empty or set to empty string \"\", selection criteria always evaluates to True. Selection criteria evaluation is done per UE with the current applicable UE <Variable> values as input. List of UE <Variable> values that are applicable to NR standalone and EN-DC, respectively, is defined in Variable Definitions section below. Selection criteria for a UE is evaluated separately for each flow using applicable flow-dependent <Variable> together with rest of applicable UE <Variable>. For UE in NR standalone flow-dependent <Variable> 5qi, arp, and snssai are applicable. For UE in EN-DC flow-dependent <Variable> qci, and arp are applicable. Selection criteria evaluates to True if any of the flows evaluates to True. If UE does not have a flow, flow-dependent <Variable> values are evaluated as unknown variable values. If selection criteria shall match combination of flow-dependent <Variable>, then <FlowExpression> and <FlowExpressionList> must be used. Note: An <ExpressionList> defined as <VariableExpression> && <VariableExpression>, for which both <VariableExpression> relate to flow-dependent <Variable>, needs special attention. Example: <ExpressionList> = \"5qi==5 && 5qi==9\" always evaluate to False for UE in NR standalone even if UE has one flow with 5qi=5 and one flow with 5qi=9. Example: <ExpressionList> = \"5qi>=7 && 5qi<=11\" will evaluate to True for UE in NR standalone if UE has any flow with 5qi between 7 and 11. <FlowExpression> is defined as \"[\"<ExpressionList>\"]\" and indicates that an <ExpressionList> is evaluated per QoS flow independent of other <ExpressionList>. Example: <FlowExpressionList> = \"[5qi==1] && [5qi==5]\" evaluates to True for UE in NR standalone if UE has any flow with 5qi=1 and any flow with 5qi=5. In the example, [5qi==1] must match one flow, and [5qi==5] must match one flow. <VariableExpression> evaluates to Unknown if <Variable> is not known or if the <Variable> value is not valid. <VariableExpression> evaluates to True or False if <Variable> value is known and valid. <Value> \"ref\" is a special <Value> of <Variable> representing <ValueList> defined via corresponding reference attribute. For <Variable> chipset, and imeisv, corresponding reference attribute is chipsetRef, and imeiSvRef respectively. If reference attribute is empty, represented <ValueList> is empty. The logical operators <AndOr> and <Not> apply three way logic as defined below: F=False; T=True; U=Unknown A=Evaluation result of <ExpressionList> or <VariableExpression> B=Evaluation result of <ExpressionList> or <VariableExpression> NOT operator: A !A ----------------- F T U U T F AND operator: A B A && B ------------------- F F F F T F F U F T F F T T T T U U U F F U T U U U U OR operator: A B A || B ------------------ F F F F T T F U U T F T T T T T U T U F U U T T U U U Variable Definitions: ================= Allowed <Value> and <RelationalOperator> depend on <Variable> with limitations given below. 5qi: 5G QoS Identifier (3GPP TS 23.501). Applicable to NR standalone. Operator: ==, !=, <=, >=, <, and >. Value: Integer in range 0..255 given in decimal. arp: Priority Level part of the Allocation and Retention Priority (3GPP TS 38.413, 3GPP TS 36.423). Applicable to both NR standalone and EN-DC. Operator: ==, !=, <=, >=, <, and >. Value: Integer in range 1..15 given in decimal. cgrole: Cell group role. Applicable to both NR standalone and EN-DC. Operator: ==, and !=. Value: mcg or scg, where mcg is only applicable to NR standalone. chipset: Chipset identifier. Applicable to both NR standalone and EN-DC. Operator: ==, and !=. Value: String in format \"<vendor>.<variant>.<version>\" matched by regular expression \"(1[0-6]|[0-9])\\\\.(6[0-4]|[1-5]?[0-9])\\\\.(12[0-8]|1[01][0-9]|[1-9]?[0-9])\", or a string constant \"ref\". Description: Chipset identifier composed of three distinct elements: - vendor: 1-2 digit decimal number in range 0..16 - variant: 1-2 digit decimal number in range 0..64 - version: 1-3 digit decimal number in range 0..128 UEs that do not support chipset identifier reporting are represented internally as 0.0.0. Example values: 0.0.0, 1.1.1, 1.2.3, 16.10.100, 16.64.128, ref. imeisv: International Mobile Station Equipment Identity Software Version. Applicable to both NR standalone and EN-DC. Operator: ==, and !=. Value: String in format \"<TAC><SNR><SVN>\" matched by regular expression \"[0-9]{10}[0-9fF]{4}[0-9]{2}\", or string constant \"ref\". Description: IMEISV composed of three distinct elements: - TAC (Type Allocation Code): 8 digit decimal number - SNR (or SN, Serial Number): 2 digit decimal number + 4 digit hexa-decimal number, last four digits are automatically masked with 0xFFFF to match with masked IMEISV - SVN (Software Version Number): 2 digit decimal number Example values: 1234567890123456, 1234567890FFFF12, 1234567890ffff12, ref. imeitac: Type Allocation Code (TAC) part of imeisv. Applicable to both NR standalone and EN-DC. Operator: ==, !=, <=, >=, <, and >. Value: 8 digit decimal number. imeisvn: Software Version Number (SVN) part of imeisv. Applicable to both NR standalone and EN-DC. Operator: ==, !=, <=, >=, <, and >. Value: 2 digit decimal number. pagingPrio: Paging Priority (3GPP TS 23.501). Applicable to NR standalone. Operator: ==, !=, <=, >=, <, and > Value: Integer in range 1..8 given in decimal. Description: Paging priority value received in NGAP Paging message. The received value is valid in UE grouping framework when performing UE group evaluation during time specified by UeGroupSelection::validityTimePagingPrio. pCellOnlyUe: Low-Band and Mid-Band PCell-only capability. Indicates whether the UE is not capable of carrier aggregation in Low-Band or Mid-Band. Only applicable when performing UE group evaluation in NR standalone Master Node. Operator: ==, and !=. Value: Integer in range 0..1 given in decimal, where 0 means false and 1 means true. Only applicable if license for Flexible UE Grouping for Limited Capability UEs is present and feature is active. plmn: Public Land and Mobile Network identifier. Applicable to both NR standalone and EN-DC. Operator: ==, and !=. Value: A string matched by regular expression \"[02-79][0-9][0-9]-[0-9][0-9][0-9]?\". Example values: 070-007, 070-07, 234-56. qci: QoSClass Identifier (3GPP TS 23.401). Applicable to EN-DC. Operator: ==, !=, <=, >=, <, and >. Value: Integer in range 0..255 given in decimal. redCapUe: Reduced Capabilities UE indicator. Applicable to NR standalone. Operator: ==, and !=. Value: Integer in range 0..1 given in decimal, where 0 means false and 1 means true. Description: RedCap UE identification received via LCID in MSG3 (see 3GPP TS 38.331). rfsp: Index to RAT/Frequency Selection Priority (3GPP TS 23.501). Applicable to NR standalone. Operator: ==, !=, <=, >=, <, and >. Value: Integer in range 1..256 given in decimal. rrcEstResCause: RRC establishment cause or RRC resume cause. Applicable to NR standalone. Operator: ==, and !=. Value: One of emergency, highPriorityAccess, mt-Access, mo-Signaling, mo-Data, mo-VoiceCall, mo-VideoCall, mo-SMS, mps-PriorityAccess, or mcs-PriorityAccess. Description: Establishment cause value received in RRC Setup Request message or resume cause received in RRC Resume Request message (see 3GPP TS 38.331). The received establishment cause or resume cause is valid in UE grouping framework when performing UE group evaluation during time specified by corresponding validity time attribute value in MO class UeGroupSelection. snssai: Single Network Slice Selection Assistance Information (3GPP TS 23.003). Applicable to NR standalone. Operator: ==, !=, <=, >=, <, and >. Value: input option 1: String in format \"<SST><SD>\" matched by regular expression [0][x][0-9a-fA-F]{8} (8 digit hexa-decimal number). Value: input option 2: Integer in range 0x0..0xffffffff given in hexadecimal. Description: S-NSSAI is composed of two distinct elements: - SST (Slice/Service Type): 2 digit hexa-decimal number - SD (Slice Differentiator): 6 digit hexa-decimal number The SD field has a reserved value \"no SD value associated with the SST\" defined as hexadecimal FFFFFF/ffffff. Example values, input option 1: - 0x050000EE (SST=0x05,SD=0x0000EE) - 0x2effffff (SST=0x2e,SD=0xffffff // no SD associated with the SST) Example values, input option 2: - 0x1 (SST=0x00,SD=0x000001) - 0x50000EE (SST=0x05,SD=0x0000EE) - 0x150000EE (SST=0x15,SD=0x0000EE) spid: Subscriber Profile ID for RAT/Frequency Priority (3GPP TS 36.300). Applicable to EN-DC. Operator: ==, !=, <=, >=, <, and >. Value: Integer in range 1..256 given in decimal. voNrUe: Low-Band and Mid-Band VoNR capability. Only applicable when performing UE group evaluation in NR standalone Master Node. Operator: ==, and !=. Value: Integer in range 0..1 given in decimal, where 0 means false and 1 means true. Operator Precedence Order: ======================= The logical and relation operators are evaluated according to the precedence order listed below. --------------------------------------------- 1 (highest precedence) < Less than <= Less than or equal > Greater than >= Greater than or equal == Equal != Not equal ------------------------------------------- 2 ! (Not) --------------------------------------------- 3 && (And) --------------------------------------------- 4 (lowest precedence) || (Or) --------------------------------------------- The NOT operator \"!\" negates the following <ParentExpressionList>, <VariableExpression>, <FlowExpression> or an <ExpressionList> encapsulated in parenthesis. Therefore, expression !a==b && c==d is equivalent to ((!(a==b)) && (c==d)) and different from !(a==b && c==d). Expression !a==b and !(a==b) are equivalent. Since AND operator \"&&\" has higher precedence than OR operator \"||\", a<b || a<c && c<d is equivalent to (a<b || (a<c && c<d)). Surround expression list including OR operator with parenthesis to force OR operator to be evaluated before AND operators outside of the expression list, for example (a<b || a<c) && c<d. Examples: ========= Simple one valued expressions: plmn == 234-56 spid == 1 cgrole == mcg arp > 3 snssai == 0xfedcba98 rrcEstResCause == mo-VoiceCall imeisv == 1234567890FFFF12 imeisv == ref //Special <value> ref represents <ValueList> defined via imeiSvRef. chipset == ref chipset == 1.1.1 //Matches all UEs with chipset identifier: vendor = 1, variant = 1 and version = 1. chipset == 0.0.0 //Matches all UEs that do not support chipset identifier reporting. Value list expressions: spid == {8,9,10,1,155} !plmn == {234-56, 434-567} chipset == {1.1.1, 1.1.2, 1.1.3, ref} //Matches all UEs with chipset identifier: vendor = 1, variant = 1 and version = 1, 2 or 3, or the corresponding vendor, variant and version defined via chipsetRef. imeisv == {1234567890FFFF12, ref, 1234567890FFFF13} //Matches all UEs with imeisv: TAC = 12345678, SNR = 90FFFF and SVN = 12 or 13, or the corresponding TAC, SN and SVN defined via imeiSvRef. Equivalent expressions using ||: (spid == 8 || spid == 9 || spid == 10 || spid == 1 || spid == 155) //Equals to spid == {8, 9, 10, 1, 155}. !(plmn == 234-56 || plmn == 434-567) //Equals to !plmn == {234-56, 434-567}. imeisv == ref || imeisv == 1234567890FFFF12|| imeisv == 1234567890FFFF13 //Equals to imeisv == {ref, 1234567890FFFF12, 1234567890FFFF13}. chipset == 1.1.1 || chipset == ref || chipset == 1.1.2 // Equals to chipset == {1.1.1, ref, 1.1.2}. Negative expressions: !5qi==1 //Matches flows with 5qi not equal to 1. 5qi!=1 //Matches flows with 5qi not equal to 1. Negative <FlowExpressions> that produce same result: [!5qi==1] //Matches flows with 5qi not equal to 1. [5qi!=1] //Matches flows with 5qi not equal to 1. <FlowExpressionList> negative expressions: !([5qi==1]) //Matches UEs that do not have flows with 5qi 1. ![5qi==1] //Matches UEs that do not have flows with 5qi 1. Mixed examples: spid == 1 && cgrole == mcg !(spid != 1 || cgrole != mcg) (spid == 8 || spid == 9 || spid == 10 || spid == 1 || spid == 155) && (plmn == 234-56 || plmn == 434-567) Precedence given by \"()\" and sequence alter the evaluation order and result: [5qi==1] && chipset==ref || imeisv==ref && [5qi==5] //Equals to ([5qi==1] && chipset==ref) || (imeisv==ref && [5qi==5]) [5qi==1] && (chipset==ref || imeisv==ref) && [5qi==5] ([5qi==1] && chipset==ref || imeisv==ref) && [5qi==5] [5qi==1] && (chipset==ref || imeisv==ref && [5qi==5]) chipset==ref || [5qi==1] && [5qi==5] && imeisv==ref Examples of selection criteria that shall be avoided since they will always be evaluated to False. <FlowExpression> can be used in these cases. 5qi==5 && 5qi==9 snssai==0x15000000 && snssai==0x17000000 arp==5 && arp==10 qci==5 && qci==9 Example of selection criteria for UE variable snssai: snssai>=15000000 && snssai<=15FFFFFF //Matches UE which has a flow with S-NSSAI SST part equal to 15 regardless of value of S-NSSAI SD part. snssai==15FFFFFF //Matches UE which has a flow with S-NSSAI SST part equal to 15 and S-NSSAI SD part value equal to FFFFFF, meaning no SD value associated with the SST. Flow expressions combined with UE variables: plmn == 234-56 && [5qi==1] && [5qi==9] //Matches UE which has plmn equal to 234-56, any QoS flow with 5qi equal to 1, and any QoS flow with 5qi equal to 9. chipset==1.5.32 && [5qi==9] && ![5qi==1] //Matches UE which has chipset identifier equal to 1.5.32, any QoS flow with 5qi equal to 9, and no QoS flow with 5qi equal to 1. [5qi==1 && snssai == 0xfedcba98] || ([5qi==2] && [snssai == 0xfedcba77]) //Matches UE which has any QoS flow with 5qi equal to 1 and snssai equal to 0xfedcba98, or has any QoS flow with 5qi equal to 2 and snssai equal to 0xfedcba77. voNrUe==1 && chipset==1.1.1 && [5qi==1] //Matches UEs with Low-Band and Mid-Band VoNR capability using chipset 1.1.1, and have an ongoing flow 5qi.; length 1..1000.";
      type string {
        length "1..1000";
      }
    }
    leaf ueMobilityGroupDefinitionId {
      description "The value component of the RDN..";
      type string;
      mandatory true;
    }
    leaf ueMobilityGroupId {
      description "UE mobility group identifier.; range 1..255.";
      type eytypes:int32_range_1-255;
      mandatory true;
    }
    leaf ueMobilityGroupPriority {
      description "Relative priority among UE mobility groups. If UE fulfills selection criteria for more than one UE mobility group, UE mobility group with the highest priority is selected. Higher value gives higher priority.; range 1..65535.";
      type eytypes:int32_range_1-65535;
      mandatory true;
    }
    leaf userLabel {
      description "Label for free use..";
      type string;
    }
  }
  grouping UeNoDrb-attributes {
    leaf ueNoDrbId {
      description "The value component of the RDN..";
      type string;
      mandatory true;
    }
  }
  grouping UeNoDrbPCellProfile-attributes {
    leaf-list reservedBy {
      description "Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance..";
      type string;
      min-elements 0;
    }
    leaf ueConfGroupType {
      description "UE configuration group type. UE configuration group type that is applied in contained UeNoDrbPCellProfileUeCfg instances..";
      type enumeration {
        enum UE_MOBILITY_GROUP;
        enum UE_SERVICE_GROUP;
        enum UE_ADMISSION_GROUP;
      }
    }
    leaf ueNoDrbPCellProfileId {
      description "The value component of the RDN..";
      type string;
      mandatory true;
    }
    leaf userLabel {
      description "Label for free use..";
      type string;
    }
  }
  grouping UeNoDrbPCellProfileUeCfg-attributes {
    leaf posUeWoPduSessionEnabled {
      description "Whether UE positioning is enabled for UE without PDU session. Only applicable if license for Positioning of UEs without PDU Session is present and feature is active. Only applicable to Low-Band and Mid-Band cells.; Default value: false.";
      type boolean;
      default "false";
    }
    leaf-list prefUeGroupList {
      description "Preference UE group list. List of preference UE group identifiers. If empty, MO instance matches preference UE group identifiers not defined in prefUeGroupList of any other MO instances under parent MO instance..";
      type eytypes:int32_range_1-255;
      ordered-by user;
      min-elements 0;
      max-elements 8;
    }
    list rsrpBetterPCell {
      key "id";
      leaf id {
        type uint32;
        description "Synthetic key for struct attribute.";
      }
      description "Downlink RSRP measurement report criteria when searching for better PCell..";
      uses ReportConfigA3Rsrp-struct;
    }
    leaf rsrpBetterPCellEnabled {
      description "Whether RSRP measurement for detecting better PCell is enabled. RSRP measurement criteria for detecting better PCell is defined by rsrpBetterPCell.; Default value: false.";
      type boolean;
      default "false";
    }
    list rsrpCritical {
      key "id";
      leaf id {
        type uint32;
        description "Synthetic key for struct attribute.";
      }
      description "RSRP measurement report criteria for detecting critical coverage..";
      uses ReportConfigA2Rsrp-struct;
    }
    leaf rsrpCriticalEnabled {
      description "Whether RSRP measurement for detecting critical coverage is enabled. RSRP measurement criteria for detecting critical coverage is defined by rsrpCritical.; Default value: false.";
      type boolean;
      default "false";
    }
    list rsrpCriticalPcOffset {
      key "id";
      leaf id {
        type uint32;
        description "Synthetic key for struct sequence entry.";
      }
      min-elements 0;
      max-elements 3;
      uses ReportConfigA1A2RsrpPcOffset-struct;
    }
    list rsrqCritical {
      key "id";
      leaf id {
        type uint32;
        description "Synthetic key for struct attribute.";
      }
      description "RSRQ measurement report criteria for detecting critical coverage..";
      uses ReportConfigA2Rsrq-struct;
    }
    leaf rsrqCriticalEnabled {
      description "Whether RSRQ measurement for detecting critical coverage is enabled. RSRQ measurement criteria for detecting critical coverage is defined by rsrqCritical.; Default value: false.";
      type boolean;
      default "false";
    }
    list sinrCritical {
      key "id";
      leaf id {
        type uint32;
        description "Synthetic key for struct attribute.";
      }
      description "SINR measurement report criteria for detecting critical coverage. Applicable for UEs supporting SINR..";
      uses ReportConfigA2Sinr-struct;
    }
    leaf sinrCriticalEnabled {
      description "Whether SINR measurement for detecting critical coverage is enabled. SINR measurement criteria for detecting critical coverage is defined by sinrCritical.; Default value: false.";
      type boolean;
      default "false";
    }
    leaf-list ueConfGroupList {
      description "UE configuration group list. List of UE configuration group identifiers. If empty, MO instance matches all UE configuration group identifiers. UE configuration group type is defined by ueConfGroupType in parent MO instance..";
      type eytypes:int32_range_1-255;
      ordered-by user;
      min-elements 0;
      max-elements 32;
    }
    leaf-list ueGroupList {
      description "UE group list. List of UE group identifiers. If empty, MO instance matches all UE group identifiers..";
      type eytypes:int32_range_1-255;
      ordered-by user;
      min-elements 0;
      max-elements 16;
    }
    leaf ueNoDrbPCellProfileUeCfgId {
      description "The value component of the RDN..";
      type string;
      mandatory true;
    }
    leaf userLabel {
      description "Label for free use..";
      type string;
    }
  }
  grouping UeServiceGroupDefinition-attributes {
    leaf chipsetRef {
      description "Reference to an instance of Chipsets MO. Special <Value> \"ref\" for <Variable> chipset in selectionCriteria represents chipset <ValueList> defined via this reference. If empty, represented chipset <ValueList> is empty..";
      type string;
    }
    leaf imeiSvRef {
      description "Reference to an instance of ImeiSvs MO. Special <Value> \"ref\" for <Variable> imeisv in selectionCriteria represents imeisv <ValueList> defined via this reference. If empty, represented imeisv <ValueList> is empty..";
      type string;
    }
    leaf selectionCriteria {
      description "UE service group selection criteria. Defines selection criteria that UE needs to fulfill to belong to the UE service group instance. If selection criteria evaluates to True, UE fulfills UE service group instance. If selection criteria evaluates to False or Unknown, UE does not fulfill UE service group instance. If selection criteria evaluates to True for more than one UE service group instance, UE belongs to the UE service group instance with highest setting of ueServiceGroupPriority. Syntax: ====== The syntax of selection criteria is defined using Backus-Naur form. <SelectionCriteria> ::= <ParentExpressionList> | \"\" <ParentExpressionList> ::= <ParentExpressionList> <AndOr> < ParentExpressionList> | <Not>? \"(\" <ParentExpressionList> \")\" | <ExpressionList> | <FlowExpressionList> <FlowExpressionList> ::= <FlowExpressionList> <AndOr> <FlowExpressionList> | <Not>? <FlowExpression> <FlowExpression> ::= \"[\"<ExpressionList>\"]\" <ExpressionList> ::= <ExpressionList> <AndOr> <ExpressionList> | <Not>? \"(\" <ExpressionList> \")\" | <Not>? <VariableExpression> <VariableExpression> ::= <Variable> <RelationalOperator> <Value> | <Variable> \"==\" \"{\" <ValueList> \"}\" <ValueList> ::= <Value> \",\" <ValueList> | <Value> <Variable> ::= \"5qi\" | \"arp\" | \"cgrole\" | \"chipset\" | \"imeisv\" | \"imeisvn\" | \"imeitac\" | \"pagingPrio\" | \"pCellOnlyUe\" | \"plmn\" | \"qci\" | \"redCapUe\" | \"rfsp\" | \"rrcEstResCause\" | \"snssai\" | \"spid\" | \"voNrUe\" <AndOr> ::= \"&&\" | \"||\" <Not> ::= \"!\" <RelationalOperator> ::= \"==\" | \"!=\" | \"<\" | \"<=\" | \">=\" | \">\" A list of possible values can be specified in the form <Variable> == {<value1>, <value2>, ... , <valueN>}. This statement is equivalent to writing (<Variable> == <value1> || <Variable> == <value2> || ... || <Variable> == <valueN>). Up to 4 <FlowExpression> can be defined in <SelectionCriteria>. Whitespaces are allowed in the string for improved readability and are removed prior to evaluation. Question mark (?) means zero or one occurrence. For example, <Not>? makes <Not> optional. Syntax is case sensitive. Semantic: ======== Selection criteria evaluation is defined by the following semantic rules. If empty or set to empty string \"\", selection criteria always evaluates to True. Selection criteria evaluation is done per UE with the current applicable UE <Variable> values as input. List of UE <Variable> values that are applicable to NR standalone and EN-DC, respectively, is defined in Variable Definitions section below. Selection criteria for a UE is evaluated separately for each flow using applicable flow-dependent <Variable> together with rest of applicable UE <Variable>. For UE in NR standalone flow-dependent <Variable> 5qi, arp, and snssai are applicable. For UE in EN-DC flow-dependent <Variable> qci, and arp are applicable. Selection criteria evaluates to True if any of the flows evaluates to True. If UE does not have a flow, flow-dependent <Variable> values are evaluated as unknown variable values. If selection criteria shall match combination of flow-dependent <Variable>, then <FlowExpression> and <FlowExpressionList> must be used. Note: An <ExpressionList> defined as <VariableExpression> && <VariableExpression>, for which both <VariableExpression> relate to flow-dependent <Variable>, needs special attention. Example: <ExpressionList> = \"5qi==5 && 5qi==9\" always evaluate to False for UE in NR standalone even if UE has one flow with 5qi=5 and one flow with 5qi=9. Example: <ExpressionList> = \"5qi>=7 && 5qi<=11\" will evaluate to True for UE in NR standalone if UE has any flow with 5qi between 7 and 11. <FlowExpression> is defined as \"[\"<ExpressionList>\"]\" and indicates that an <ExpressionList> is evaluated per QoS flow independent of other <ExpressionList>. Example: <FlowExpressionList> = \"[5qi==1] && [5qi==5]\" evaluates to True for UE in NR standalone if UE has any flow with 5qi=1 and any flow with 5qi=5. In the example, [5qi==1] must match one flow, and [5qi==5] must match one flow. <VariableExpression> evaluates to Unknown if <Variable> is not known or if the <Variable> value is not valid. <VariableExpression> evaluates to True or False if <Variable> value is known and valid. <Value> \"ref\" is a special <Value> of <Variable> representing <ValueList> defined via corresponding reference attribute. For <Variable> chipset, and imeisv, corresponding reference attribute is chipsetRef, and imeiSvRef respectively. If reference attribute is empty, represented <ValueList> is empty. The logical operators <AndOr> and <Not> apply three way logic as defined below: F=False; T=True; U=Unknown A=Evaluation result of <ExpressionList> or <VariableExpression> B=Evaluation result of <ExpressionList> or <VariableExpression> NOT operator: A !A ----------------- F T U U T F AND operator: A B A && B ------------------- F F F F T F F U F T F F T T T T U U U F F U T U U U U OR operator: A B A || B ------------------ F F F F T T F U U T F T T T T T U T U F U U T T U U U Variable Definitions: ================= Allowed <Value> and <RelationalOperator> depend on <Variable> with limitations given below. 5qi: 5G QoS Identifier (3GPP TS 23.501). Applicable to NR standalone. Operator: ==, !=, <=, >=, <, and >. Value: Integer in range 0..255 given in decimal. arp: Priority Level part of the Allocation and Retention Priority (3GPP TS 38.413, 3GPP TS 36.423). Applicable to both NR standalone and EN-DC. Operator: ==, !=, <=, >=, <, and >. Value: Integer in range 1..15 given in decimal. cgrole: Cell group role. Applicable to both NR standalone and EN-DC. Operator: ==, and !=. Value: mcg or scg, where mcg is only applicable to NR standalone. chipset: Chipset identifier. Applicable to both NR standalone and EN-DC. Operator: ==, and !=. Value: String in format \"<vendor>.<variant>.<version>\" matched by regular expression \"(1[0-6]|[0-9])\\\\.(6[0-4]|[1-5]?[0-9])\\\\.(12[0-8]|1[01][0-9]|[1-9]?[0-9])\", or a string constant \"ref\". Description: Chipset identifier composed of three distinct elements: - vendor: 1-2 digit decimal number in range 0..16 - variant: 1-2 digit decimal number in range 0..64 - version: 1-3 digit decimal number in range 0..128 UEs that do not support chipset identifier reporting are represented internally as 0.0.0. Example values: 0.0.0, 1.1.1, 1.2.3, 16.10.100, 16.64.128, ref. imeisv: International Mobile Station Equipment Identity Software Version. Applicable to both NR standalone and EN-DC. Operator: ==, and !=. Value: String in format \"<TAC><SNR><SVN>\" matched by regular expression \"[0-9]{10}[0-9fF]{4}[0-9]{2}\", or string constant \"ref\". Description: IMEISV composed of three distinct elements: - TAC (Type Allocation Code): 8 digit decimal number - SNR (or SN, Serial Number): 2 digit decimal number + 4 digit hexa-decimal number, last four digits are automatically masked with 0xFFFF to match with masked IMEISV - SVN (Software Version Number): 2 digit decimal number Example values: 1234567890123456, 1234567890FFFF12, 1234567890ffff12, ref. imeitac: Type Allocation Code (TAC) part of imeisv. Applicable to both NR standalone and EN-DC. Operator: ==, !=, <=, >=, <, and >. Value: 8 digit decimal number. imeisvn: Software Version Number (SVN) part of imeisv. Applicable to both NR standalone and EN-DC. Operator: ==, !=, <=, >=, <, and >. Value: 2 digit decimal number. pagingPrio: Paging Priority (3GPP TS 23.501). Applicable to NR standalone. Operator: ==, !=, <=, >=, <, and > Value: Integer in range 1..8 given in decimal. Description: Paging priority value received in NGAP Paging message. The received value is valid in UE grouping framework when performing UE group evaluation during time specified by UeGroupSelection::validityTimePagingPrio. plmn: Public Land and Mobile Network identifier. Applicable to both NR standalone and EN-DC. Operator: ==, and !=. Value: A string matched by regular expression \"[02-79][0-9][0-9]-[0-9][0-9][0-9]?\". Example values: 070-007, 070-07, 234-56. qci: QoSClass Identifier (3GPP TS 23.401). Applicable to EN-DC. Operator: ==, !=, <=, >=, <, and >. Value: Integer in range 0..255 given in decimal. redCapUe: Reduced Capabilities UE indicator. Applicable to NR standalone. Operator: ==, and !=. Value: Integer in range 0..1 given in decimal, where 0 means false and 1 means true. Description: RedCap UE identification received via LCID in MSG3 (see 3GPP TS 38.331). pCellOnlyUe: Low-Band and Mid-Band PCell-only capability. Indicates whether the UE is not capable of carrier aggregation in Low-Band or Mid-Band. Only applicable when performing UE group evaluation in NR standalone Master Node. Operator: ==, and !=. Value: Integer in range 0..1 given in decimal, where 0 means false and 1 means true. Only applicable if license for Flexible UE Grouping for Limited Capability UEs is present and feature is active. rfsp: Index to RAT/Frequency Selection Priority (3GPP TS 23.501). Applicable to NR standalone. Operator: ==, !=, <=, >=, <, and >. Value: Integer in range 1..256 given in decimal. rrcEstResCause: RRC establishment cause or RRC resume cause. Applicable to NR standalone. Operator: ==, and !=. Value: One of emergency, highPriorityAccess, mt-Access, mo-Signaling, mo-Data, mo-VoiceCall, mo-VideoCall, mo-SMS, mps-PriorityAccess, or mcs-PriorityAccess. Description: Establishment cause value received in RRC Setup Request message or resume cause received in RRC Resume Request message (see 3GPP TS 38.331). The received establishment cause or resume cause is valid in UE grouping framework when performing UE group evaluation during time specified by corresponding validity time attribute value in MO class UeGroupSelection. snssai: Single Network Slice Selection Assistance Information (3GPP TS 23.003). Applicable to NR standalone. Operator: ==, !=, <=, >=, <, and >. Value: input option 1: String in format \"<SST><SD>\" matched by regular expression [0][x][0-9a-fA-F]{8} (8 digit hexa-decimal number). Value: input option 2: Integer in range 0x0..0xffffffff given in hexadecimal. Description: S-NSSAI is composed of two distinct elements: - SST (Slice/Service Type): 2 digit hexa-decimal number - SD (Slice Differentiator): 6 digit hexa-decimal number The SD field has a reserved value \"no SD value associated with the SST\" defined as hexadecimal FFFFFF/ffffff. Example values, input option 1: - 0x050000EE (SST=0x05,SD=0x0000EE) - 0x2effffff (SST=0x2e,SD=0xffffff // no SD associated with the SST) Example values, input option 2: - 0x1 (SST=0x00,SD=0x000001) - 0x50000EE (SST=0x05,SD=0x0000EE) - 0x150000EE (SST=0x15,SD=0x0000EE) spid: Subscriber Profile ID for RAT/Frequency Priority (3GPP TS 36.300). Applicable to EN-DC. Operator: ==, !=, <=, >=, <, and >. Value: Integer in range 1..256 given in decimal. voNrUe: Low-Band and Mid-Band VoNR capability. Only applicable when performing UE group evaluation in NR standalone Master Node. Operator: ==, and !=. Value: Integer in range 0..1 given in decimal, where 0 means false and 1 means true. Operator Precedence Order: ======================= The logical and relation operators are evaluated according to the precedence order listed below. --------------------------------------------- 1 (highest precedence) < Less than <= Less than or equal > Greater than >= Greater than or equal == Equal != Not equal ------------------------------------------- 2 ! (Not) --------------------------------------------- 3 && (And) --------------------------------------------- 4 (lowest precedence) || (Or) --------------------------------------------- The NOT operator \"!\" negates the following <ParentExpressionList>, <VariableExpression>, <FlowExpression> or an <ExpressionList> encapsulated in parenthesis. Therefore, expression !a==b && c==d is equivalent to ((!(a==b)) && (c==d)) and different from !(a==b && c==d). Expression !a==b and !(a==b) are equivalent. Since AND operator \"&&\" has higher precedence than OR operator \"||\", a<b || a<c && c<d is equivalent to (a<b || (a<c && c<d)). Surround expression list including OR operator with parenthesis to force OR operator to be evaluated before AND operators outside of the expression list, for example (a<b || a<c) && c<d. Examples: ========= Simple one valued expressions: plmn == 234-56 spid == 1 cgrole == mcg arp > 3 snssai == 0xfedcba98 rrcEstResCause == mo-VoiceCall imeisv == 1234567890FFFF12 imeisv == ref //Special <value> ref represents <ValueList> defined via imeiSvRef. chipset == ref chipset == 1.1.1 //Matches all UEs with chipset identifier: vendor = 1, variant = 1 and version = 1. chipset == 0.0.0 //Matches all UEs that do not support chipset identifier reporting. Value list expressions: spid == {8,9,10,1,155} !plmn == {234-56, 434-567} chipset == {1.1.1, 1.1.2, 1.1.3, ref} //Matches all UEs with chipset identifier: vendor = 1, variant = 1 and version = 1, 2 or 3, or the corresponding vendor, variant and version defined via chipsetRef. imeisv == {1234567890FFFF12, ref, 1234567890FFFF13} //Matches all UEs with imeisv: TAC = 12345678, SNR = 90FFFF and SVN = 12 or 13, or the corresponding TAC, SN and SVN defined via imeiSvRef. Equivalent expressions using ||: (spid == 8 || spid == 9 || spid == 10 || spid == 1 || spid == 155) //Equals to spid == {8, 9, 10, 1, 155}. !(plmn == 234-56 || plmn == 434-567) //Equals to !plmn == {234-56, 434-567}. imeisv == ref || imeisv == 1234567890FFFF12|| imeisv == 1234567890FFFF13 //Equals to imeisv == {ref, 1234567890FFFF12, 1234567890FFFF13}. chipset == 1.1.1 || chipset == ref || chipset == 1.1.2 // Equals to chipset == {1.1.1, ref, 1.1.2}. Negative expressions: !5qi==1 //Matches flows with 5qi not equal to 1. 5qi!=1 //Matches flows with 5qi not equal to 1. Negative <FlowExpressions> that produce same result: [!5qi==1] //Matches flows with 5qi not equal to 1. [5qi!=1] //Matches flows with 5qi not equal to 1. <FlowExpressionList> negative expressions: !([5qi==1]) //Matches UEs that do not have flows with 5qi 1. ![5qi==1] //Matches UEs that do not have flows with 5qi 1. Mixed examples: spid == 1 && cgrole == mcg !(spid != 1 || cgrole != mcg) (spid == 8 || spid == 9 || spid == 10 || spid == 1 || spid == 155) && (plmn == 234-56 || plmn == 434-567) Precedence given by \"()\" and sequence alter the evaluation order and result: [5qi==1] && chipset==ref || imeisv==ref && [5qi==5] //Equals to ([5qi==1] && chipset==ref) || (imeisv==ref && [5qi==5]) [5qi==1] && (chipset==ref || imeisv==ref) && [5qi==5] ([5qi==1] && chipset==ref || imeisv==ref) && [5qi==5] [5qi==1] && (chipset==ref || imeisv==ref && [5qi==5]) chipset==ref || [5qi==1] && [5qi==5] && imeisv==ref Examples of selection criteria that shall be avoided since they will always be evaluated to False. <FlowExpression> can be used in these cases. 5qi==5 && 5qi==9 snssai==0x15000000 && snssai==0x17000000 arp==5 && arp==10 qci==5 && qci==9 Example of selection criteria for UE variable snssai: snssai>=15000000 && snssai<=15FFFFFF //Matches UE which has a flow with S-NSSAI SST part equal to 15 regardless of value of S-NSSAI SD part. snssai==15FFFFFF //Matches UE which has a flow with S-NSSAI SST part equal to 15 and S-NSSAI SD part value equal to FFFFFF, meaning no SD value associated with the SST. Flow expressions combined with UE variables: plmn == 234-56 && [5qi==1] && [5qi==9] //Matches UE which has plmn equal to 234-56, any QoS flow with 5qi equal to 1, and any QoS flow with 5qi equal to 9. chipset==1.5.32 && [5qi==9] && ![5qi==1] //Matches UE which has chipset identifier equal to 1.5.32, any QoS flow with 5qi equal to 9, and no QoS flow with 5qi equal to 1. [5qi==1 && snssai == 0xfedcba98] || ([5qi==2] && [snssai == 0xfedcba77]) //Matches UE which has any QoS flow with 5qi equal to 1 and snssai equal to 0xfedcba98, or has any QoS flow with 5qi equal to 2 and snssai equal to 0xfedcba77. voNrUe==1 && chipset==1.1.1 && [5qi==1] //Matches UEs with Low-Band and Mid-Band VoNR capability using chipset 1.1.1, and have an ongoing flow 5qi.; length 1..1000.";
      type string {
        length "1..1000";
      }
    }
    leaf ueServiceGroupDefinitionId {
      description "The value component of the RDN..";
      type string;
      mandatory true;
    }
    leaf ueServiceGroupId {
      description "UE service group identifier.; range 1..255.";
      type eytypes:int32_range_1-255;
      mandatory true;
    }
    leaf ueServiceGroupPriority {
      description "Relative priority among UE service groups. If UE fulfills selection criteria for more than one UE service group, UE service group with the highest priority is selected. Higher value gives higher priority.; range 1..65535.";
      type eytypes:int32_range_1-65535;
      mandatory true;
    }
    leaf userLabel {
      description "Label for free use..";
      type string;
    }
  }
  grouping UeUlResMon-attributes {
    leaf ueUlResMonId {
      description "The value component of the RDN..";
      type string;
      mandatory true;
    }
  }
  grouping UlBufferMonCfg-attributes {
    leaf-list reservedBy {
      description "Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance..";
      type string;
      min-elements 0;
    }
    leaf ulBsVolThresh {
      description "Buffer size threshold for uplink data volume for each LCG in BSR. If 0, uplink volume buffer monitoring is disabled.; Default value: 0.";
      type int32 {
        range "0 | 10..20 | 22..23 | 25..26 | 28 | 30 | 32 | 34 | 36 | 38 | 40 | 43 | 46 | 49 | 52 | 55 | 59 | 62 | 66 | 71 | 75 | 80 | 85 | 91 | 97 | 103 | 110 | 117 | 124 | 132 | 141 | 150 | 160 | 170 | 181 | 193 | 205 | 218 | 233 | 248 | 264 | 281 | 299 | 318 | 339 | 361 | 384 | 409 | 436 | 464 | 494 | 526 | 560 | 597 | 635 | 677 | 720 | 767 | 817 | 870 | 926 | 987 | 1051 | 1119 | 1191 | 1269 | 1351 | 1439 | 1532 | 1631 | 1737 | 1850 | 1970 | 2098 | 2234 | 2379 | 2533 | 2698 | 2873 | 3059 | 3258 | 3469 | 3694 | 3934 | 4189 | 4461 | 4751 | 5059 | 5387 | 5737 | 6109 | 6506 | 6928 | 7378 | 7857 | 8367 | 8910 | 9488 | 10104 | 10760 | 11458 | 12202 | 12994 | 13838 | 14736 | 15692 | 16711 | 17795 | 18951 | 20181 | 21491 | 22885 | 24371 | 25953 | 27638 | 29431 | 31342 | 33376 | 35543 | 37850 | 40307 | 42923 | 45709 | 48676 | 51836 | 55200 | 58784 | 62599 | 66663 | 70990 | 75598 | 80505 | 85730 | 91295 | 97221 | 103532 | 110252 | 117409 | 125030 | 133146 | 141789 | 150992 | 160793 | 171231 | 182345 | 194182 | 206786 | 220209 | 234503 | 249725 | 265935 | 283197 | 301579 | 321155 | 342002 | 364202 | 387842 | 413018 | 439827 | 468377 | 498780 | 531156 | 565634 | 602350 | 641449 | 683087 | 727427 | 774645 | 824928 | 878475 | 935498 | 996222 | 1060888 | 1129752 | 1203085 | 1281179 | 1364342 | 1452903 | 1547213 | 1647644 | 1754595 | 1868488 | 1989774 | 2118933 | 2256475 | 2402946 | 2558924 | 2725027 | 2901912 | 3090279 | 3290873 | 3504487 | 3731968 | 3974215 | 4232186 | 4506902 | 4799451 | 5110989 | 5442750 | 5796046 | 6172275 | 6572925 | 6999582 | 7453933 | 7937777 | 8453028 | 9001725 | 9586039 | 10208280 | 10870913 | 11576557 | 12328006 | 13128233 | 13980403 | 14887889 | 15854280 | 16883401 | 17979324 | 19146385 | 20389201 | 21712690 | 23122088 | 24622972 | 26221280 | 27923336 | 29735875 | 31666069 | 33721553 | 35910462 | 38241455 | 40723756 | 43367187 | 46182206 | 49179951 | 52372284 | 55771835 | 59392055 | 63247269 | 67352729 | 71724679 | 76380419 | 81338368";
      }
      default "0";
      units "byte";
    }
    leaf ulBufferMonCfgId {
      description "The value component of the RDN..";
      type string;
      mandatory true;
    }
  }
  grouping UlDataSplit-attributes {
    leaf-list reservedBy {
      description "Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance..";
      type string;
      min-elements 0;
    }
    leaf ueConfGroupType {
      description "UE configuration group type. UE configuration group type that is applied in contained UlDataSplitUeCfg instances..";
      type enumeration {
        enum UE_MOBILITY_GROUP;
        enum UE_SERVICE_GROUP;
        enum UE_ADMISSION_GROUP;
      }
    }
    leaf ulDataSplitId {
      description "The value component of the RDN..";
      type string;
      mandatory true;
    }
    leaf userLabel {
      description "Label for free use..";
      type string;
    }
  }
  grouping UlDataSplitUeCfg-attributes {
    leaf initialUlPrimaryPathMode {
      description "Uplink primary path mode for initial configuration at dual connectivity setup. Applicable to both EN-DC and NR-DC. Uplink primary path is configured as follows at setup of secondary node-terminated split DRB. SCG in following cases: - value is SCG. - value is COVERAGE_BASED and PSCell uplink quality level is above sum of UlCgSwitchCfg::ulScgLowQualThresh and UlCgSwitchCfg::ulScgLowQualHyst. - value is COVERAGE_BASED and PSCell RSRP level is above InitialCgUeCfg::ulScgInitialLowRsrpThresh. - value is COVERAGE_BASED and PSCell uplink quality and PSCell RSRP are not available. MCG in following cases: - value is MCG. - value is COVERAGE_BASED and PSCell uplink quality level is below UlCgSwitchCfg::ulScgLowQualThresh. - value is COVERAGE_BASED and PSCell RSRP level is below InitialCgUeCfg::ulScgInitialLowRsrpThresh. Value COVERAGE_BASED is only applicable if license for Service-Adaptive Uplink User Plane Profile feature is present and feature is active. Otherwise, COVERAGE_BASED is handled as SCG..";
      type enumeration {
        enum MCG;
        enum COVERAGE_BASED;
        enum SCG;
      }
    }
    leaf-list prefUeGroupList {
      description "Preference UE group list. List of preference UE group identifiers. If empty, MO instance matches preference UE group identifiers not defined in prefUeGroupList of any other MO instances under parent MO instance..";
      type eytypes:int32_range_1-255;
      ordered-by user;
      min-elements 0;
      max-elements 8;
    }
    leaf-list ueConfGroupList {
      description "UE configuration group list. List of UE configuration group identifiers. If empty, MO instance matches all UE configuration group identifiers. UE configuration group type is defined by ueConfGroupType in parent MO instance..";
      type eytypes:int32_range_1-255;
      ordered-by user;
      min-elements 0;
      max-elements 32;
    }
    leaf-list ueGroupList {
      description "UE group list. List of UE group identifiers. If empty, MO instance matches all UE group identifiers..";
      type eytypes:int32_range_1-255;
      ordered-by user;
      min-elements 0;
      max-elements 16;
    }
    leaf ulDataSplitThreshMcg {
      description "Buffer threshold for uplink PDCP split when primary path is MCG. Buffer level where capable UE instances can split data on both main and secondary leg when primary path is MCG. A capable UE is a UE with dual connectivity supporting split DRB with uplink on both MCG and SCG. This UE can submit uplink PDCP PDUs to both primary RLC entity and secondary RLC entity if total amount of PDCP and RLC data volume for initial transmission in two associated RLC entities is equal or greater than used threshold. Following settings are possible: - If empty, value according to ulDataSplitThreshScg is used. - If 0, uplink PDCP split is always active for capable UE instances. - If -1, used threshold is infinity meaning that PDCP split is not allowed even for capable UE instances. - Value -1 is recommended when DcUlCfg::ulPrimaryPathMode is set to SCG, UlCgSwitchCfg::ulCgSwitchMode is not DISABLED and a low value is set for UlCgSwitchCfg::ulScgLowQualThresh. - Values 0 to 1600 are only recommended for operators for temporary testing purposes. If UlDataSplitUeCfg=Base instance under UlDataSplit=Default_nrdc instance is created automatically, value is -1. Applicable to capable EN-DC and NR-DC UEs. Only applicable if license for LTE-NR Uplink Aggregation is present and feature is active..";
      type int32 {
        range "-1..0 | 100 | 200 | 400 | 800 | 1600 | 3200 | 6400 | 12800 | 25600 | 51200 | 102400 | 204800 | 409600 | 819200 | 1228800 | 1638400 | 2457600 | 3276800 | 4096000 | 4915200 | 5734400 | 6553600";
      }
      units "Byte";
    }
    leaf ulDataSplitThreshScg {
      description "Buffer threshold for uplink PDCP split when primary path is SCG and RSRP or uplink quality is good. Buffer level where capable UE instances can split data on both MCG and SCG when primary path is SCG and PSCell uplink quality or PSCell RSRP level is good, or PSCell uplink quality and PSCell RSRP are not available. A capable UE is a UE with dual connectivity supporting split DRB with uplink on both MCG and SCG. This UE can submit uplink PDCP PDUs to both primary RLC entity and secondary RLC entity if total amount of PDCP and RLC data volume for initial transmission in two associated RLC entities is equal or greater than used threshold. PSCell quality is considered good when PSCell quality level is above the sum of UlCgSwitchCfg::ulScgLowQualThresh and UlCgSwitchCfg::ulScgLowQualHyst. PSCell RSRP is considered good when target PSCell RSRP level is above InitialCgUeCfg::ulScgInitialLowRsrpThresh. If 0, uplink PDCP split is always active for capable UE instances. If -1, used threshold is infinity meaning that PDCP split is not allowed even for capable UE instances. If UlDataSplitUeCfg=Base instance under UlDataSplit=Default_nrdc instance is created automatically, value is -1. Applicable to capable EN-DC and NR-DC UE instances. Only applicable if license for LTE-NR Uplink Aggregation is present and feature is active.; Default value: 51200.";
      type int32 {
        range "-1..0 | 100 | 200 | 400 | 800 | 1600 | 3200 | 6400 | 12800 | 25600 | 51200 | 102400 | 204800 | 409600 | 819200 | 1228800 | 1638400 | 2457600 | 3276800 | 4096000 | 4915200 | 5734400 | 6553600";
      }
      default "51200";
      units "Byte";
    }
    leaf ulDataSplitThreshScgLow {
      description "Buffer threshold for uplink PDCP split when primary path is SCG and RSRP or uplink quality is low. Buffer level where capable UE instances can split data on both main and secondary leg when primary path is SCG and PSCell uplink quality or PSCell RSRP level is low. A capable UE is a UE with dual connectivity supporting split DRB with uplink on both MCG and SCG. This UE can submit uplink PDCP PDUs to both primary RLC entity and secondary RLC entity if total amount of PDCP and RLC data volume for initial transmission in two associated RLC entities is equal or greater than used threshold. PSCell quality is considered low when PSCell quality level is below UlCgSwitchCfg::ulScgLowQualThresh. PSCell RSRP is considered low when target PSCell RSRP level is below InitialCgUeCfg::ulScgInitialLowRsrpThresh. If 0, uplink PDCP split is always active for capable UE instances. If -1, used threshold is infinity meaning that PDCP split is not allowed even for capable UE instances. Applicable to capable EN-DC and NR-DC UE instances. Only applicable if license for following features are present and features are active: - LTE-NR Uplink Aggregation. - Service-Adaptive Uplink User Plane Profile. If license for Service-Adaptive Uplink User Plane Profile is not present or feature is not active, value of ulDataSplitThreshScg is used.; Default value: 3200.";
      type int32 {
        range "-1..0 | 100 | 200 | 400 | 800 | 1600 | 3200 | 6400 | 12800 | 25600 | 51200 | 102400 | 204800 | 409600 | 819200 | 1228800 | 1638400 | 2457600 | 3276800 | 4096000 | 4915200 | 5734400 | 6553600";
      }
      default "3200";
      units "Byte";
    }
    leaf ulDataSplitUeCfgId {
      description "The value component of the RDN..";
      type string;
      mandatory true;
    }
    leaf userLabel {
      description "Label for free use..";
      type string;
    }
  }
  grouping UlQualMcpcMeasCfg-attributes {
    leaf-list reservedBy {
      description "Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance..";
      type string;
      min-elements 0;
    }
    list ulQualCritical {
      key "id";
      leaf id {
        type uint32;
        description "Synthetic key for struct attribute.";
      }
      description "Configuration of critical uplink radio quality measurement for SpCell. Used for Mobility Control at Poor Coverage (MCPC)..";
      uses UlQualMcpcCritical-struct;
    }
    leaf ulQualMcpcMeasCfgId {
      description "The value component of the RDN..";
      type string;
      mandatory true;
    }
    list ulQualSearchZone {
      key "id";
      leaf id {
        type uint32;
        description "Synthetic key for struct attribute.";
      }
      description "Configuration of search zone uplink radio quality measurement for SpCell. Used for Mobility Control at Poor Coverage (MCPC)..";
      uses UlQualMcpcSearchZone-struct;
    }
    leaf userLabel {
      description "Label for free use..";
      type string;
    }
  }
}
